blueprints to add emotion-based response options:\n\n## Data Table Structure Modification\n\nYour existing Data Table (`DT_Dialogue`) needs to add an emotion field to track NPC emotional responses. Modify your dialogue row struct to include:\n\n1. **Add new column**: `Emotion` (type: Name or Text) - Values like \"Happy\", \"Angry\", \"Sad\", \"Neutral\", etc.\n\n## BP_NPC1 Modifications\n\n**No changes needed** - Your BP_NPC1 already passes dialogue data properly through the `OptionSelected` event, which will automatically handle the new emotion field once it's in the data table.\n\n## WB_Dialogue Modifications\n\nAdd these changes to display and handle emotion-based text:\n\n### 1. Add Widget Components\nIn the Widget Designer, add:\n- **TextBlock** named `EmotionLabel` next to the speaker name (to show current NPC emotion)\n- Style it distinctly (different color/size) to indicate emotional state\n\n### 2. Add Variable\n- **Variable**: `CurrentEmotion` (Type: Text) - stores the NPC's current emotional state\n\n### 3. Modify EventGraph\n\n**In the Construct event**:\n- After setting `Speakername` and `DialogueText`, add a SetText node for `EmotionLabel` using the `CurrentEmotion` variable\n- Format it like: `[Emotion]` or `(Emotion)` to visually separate it\n\n**Create new Custom Event**: `UpdateDialogueWithEmotion`\n- **Inputs**: \n  - `InText` (Text) - the dialogue text\n  - `InEmotion` (Text) - the emotion state\n- **Logic**:\n  - Set `DialogueText` to `InText`\n  - Set `EmotionLabel` text to formatted emotion (e.g., `\"[\" + InEmotion + \"]\"`)\n  - Store `InEmotion` in `CurrentEmotion` variable\n\n## Data Table Example Structure\n\nYour rows should now look like:\n\n| Row | Dialogue | Emotion | End Dialogue | Openended Dialogue | Openended Dialogue Options |\n|-----|----------|---------|--------------|-------------------|---------------------------|\n| 1 | \"This is working?\" | Curious | true | true | [Array with options] |\n| 2 | \"Nice. I'm happy its working