r (e.g., \"Angry\", \"Friendly\", \"Sarcastic\")\n- `PlayerDialogue` (Text) - What the player character actually says when this option is selected\n- Keep existing: `Row`, `DataTable` (for NPC's response)\n\n### 2. WB_Dialogue Modifications\n\n**Add Variable**:\n- `PlayerCharacterName` (Text) - The player's character name for display\n\n**Modify the options display**:\n- Currently, options show `OptionName` directly\n- Change to show the emotion label instead (e.g., \"😠 Confront them\" instead of exact text)\n\n**Add new Custom Event**: `ShowPlayerResponse`\n- **Inputs**: \n  - `PlayerText` (Text) - what the player actually says\n- **Logic**:\n  - Temporarily show the player's spoken dialogue in the dialogue box\n  - Use a Delay (2-3 seconds) or wait for player input\n  - Then proceed to show NPC's response\n\n### 3. BP_NPC1 Modifications\n\n**In `OptionSelected` Event**:\n\nAfter getting the data table row and before showing the NPC's response:\n1. Extract the `PlayerDialogue` from the selected option\n2. Call `ShowPlayerResponse` on the DialogueWidget with the player's text\n3. After the delay/confirmation, continue with the NPC's response as normal\n\n### 4. WB_Options Blueprint (the option buttons)\n\nThis blueprint needs to:\n- Display the emotion label instead of the full response text\n- Pass the player dialogue data when clicked (so BP_NPC1 can show it before the NPC responds)\n\n## Example Data Table Row Structure\n\n```\nRow 1:\n- Dialogue: \"This is working?\"\n- openendedDialogueOptions: [\n    {\n      OptionEmotion: \"Confident\",\n      PlayerDialogue: \"Yes, everything is functioning perfectly!\",\n      Row: \"2\",\n      DataTable: DT_Dialogue\n    },\n    {\n      OptionEmotion: \"Uncertain\", \n      PlayerDialogue: \"I... I think so? Maybe?\",\n      Row: \"3\",\n      DataTable: DT_Dialogue\n    },\n    {\n      OptionEmotion: \"Sarcastic\",\n      PlayerDialogue: \"Oh yeah, totally working. Can't you tell?\",\n      Row: \"4\", \n      DataTable: DT_Dialogue\n    }\n  ]\n```\n\n## Visual Flow Example\n\n**Before click:**\n```\nNPC: \"This is working?\"\n\n[💪 Confident]  [😰 Uncertain]  [😏 Sarcastic]\n```\n\n**After clicking \"Confident\":**\n```\nPlayer: \"Yes, everything is functioning perfectly!\"\n(brief pause or press to continue)\n\nNPC: \"Nice. I'm happy it's working\"\n```\n\nThis way, players choose how their character responds emotionally, but don't see the exact words until after selection—creating more natural roleplay and surprise in the dialogue.\n\nWould you like me to provide the specific step-by-step implementation for modifying the data table structure and blueprint logic?","state":"done"}],"role":"assistant","metadata":{"createdAt":"1769169259911"}},{"id":"5bdd24ad-45fa-40b0-8152-290ebb4ea947","parts":[{"type":"text","text":"<IMPORTANT_RULE>When calling generate_blueprint you must never edit or create blueprint graphs on Blueprints that were not created using create_assets in this session. If the user asks you to edit an existing blueprint, inform them that you cannot edit blueprints not created by Aura unless they enable \"Edit Existing Blueprints\" in settings.</IMPORTANT_RULE>","isHiddenInUI":true},{"type":"text","text":"<RelevantContext> Current window info:\n{\r\n\t\"open_windows\": [\r\n\t\t\"DialogueGame - Unreal Editor\",\r\n\t\t\"Plugins\",\r\n\t\t\"WB_Dialogue\",\r\n\t\t\"Aura Chat\"\r\n\t],\r\n\t\"level\": \"PersistentLevel\",\r\n\t\"current_level_path\": \"/Game/ThirdPerson/Lvl_ThirdPerson.Lvl_ThirdPerson\"\r\n}\n<UE_context_object>/Game/Dialogue/WB_Dialogue.WB_Dialogue\nBlueprint Name: WB_Dialogue\nPath: /Game/Dialogue/WB_Dialogue.WB_Dialogue\nParent Class: UserWidget\nVariables:\n- DialogueUsername (text)\n- Dialogue (text)\nBlueprint Graph: EventGraph\n  Node: Event: Construct [No Inputs] (EventGraph.K2Node_Event_1)\n    (ThisNode)->(EventGraph.K2Node_CallFunction_0)\n  Node: VariableGet (EventGraph.K2Node_VariableGet_0)\n \n... [Truncated: 67 more lines] </UE_context_obje