gue\n  },\n  {\n    OptionEmotion: \"Uncertain\",\n    PlayerDialogue: \"I... I think so? Maybe?\",\n    Row: \"3\",\n    DataTable: DT_Dialogue\n  }\n]\n```\n\n### **Step 3: Modify WB_Options Blueprint**\n\nThis widget displays individual response options.\n\n**Add Variable:**\n- **`PlayerDialogue`** (Type: Text) - Store the player's actual response text\n\n**Modify the widget initialization:**\n1. When creating the option button, instead of showing `OptionName`, display `OptionEmotion`\n2. Store `PlayerDialogue` in the new variable\n3. When the button is clicked, pass both the `Row`/`DataTable` AND the `PlayerDialogue` back to BP_NPC1\n\n**Update button click event:**\n- The event dispatcher or function call should now include `PlayerDialogue` as a parameter\n\n### **Step 4: Modify WB_Dialogue Blueprint**\n\n**Add Variables:**\n- **`PlayerCharacterName`** (Type: Text, Default: \"Player\") - For displaying player name\n- **`IsShowingPlayerResponse`** (Type: Boolean) - Track if showing player or NPC dialogue\n\n**Add Custom Event: `ShowPlayerResponse`**\n- **Inputs:**\n  - `PlayerText` (Text)\n  \n**Graph Logic:**\n```\nShowPlayerResponse Event\n  ├─→ Set Speakername text to PlayerCharacterName\n  ├─→ Set DialogueText to PlayerText\n  ├─→ Set IsShowingPlayerResponse = true\n  └─→ (Optional) Add visual indicator this is player speaking\n```\n\n**Modify Construct Event:**\n- Initialize `PlayerCharacterName` if needed\n- Set up initial display state\n\n### **Step 5: Modify BP_NPC1 Blueprint**\n\n**In the `OptionSelected` Event**, restructure the flow:\n\n**Current flow:**\n```\nOptionSelected (RowName, DataTable)\n  └─→ GetDataTableRow\n      └─→ UpdateDialogue (shows NPC response immediately)\n```\n\n**New flow:**\n```\nOptionSelected (RowName, DataTable, PlayerDialogue)\n  ├─→ ShowPlayerResponse (PlayerDialogue)\n  ├─→ Delay (2.0 seconds) or WaitForInput\n  ├─→ GetDataTableRow (RowName, DataTable)\n  └─→ UpdateDialogue (NPC's response)\n```\n\n**Detailed nodes:**\n1. **After receiving OptionSelected event:**\n   - Call `ShowPlayerResponse` on DialogueWidget with `PlayerDialogue` parameter\n   \n2. **Add Delay node** (2-3 seconds) or create input-based continuation\n   \n3. **After delay:**\n   - Call `ClearChildren` on OptionsScrollBox\n   - Call `GetDataTableRow` with the provided RowName/DataTable\n   - Break the result struct\n   - Call `UpdateDialogue` with NPC's dialogue text\n   - Set variables (RowName, DataTable, EndDialogue, etc.)\n   - If OpenendedDialogue is true, create new option buttons\n\n**In the `Interact` Event:**\n- When first creating dialogue widget, set the `PlayerCharacterName` variable\n- This can be retrieved from your player character or game instance\n\n### **Step 6: Update WB_Options Creation in BP_NPC1**\n\nWhen creating option widgets in the ForEach loop:\n\n**Current:**\n```\nCreateWidget (WB_Options)\n  └─→ Set Name parameter\n```\n\n**New:**\n```\nCreateWidget (WB_Options)\n  ├─→ Set Name parameter to OptionEmotion (not OptionName)\n  ├─→ Set PlayerDialogue parameter\n  ├─→ Set RowName parameter\n  └─→ Set DataTable parameter\n```\n\n### **Step 7: Visual Polish (Optional)**\n\n**In WB_Dialogue:**\n- Add a colored bar or icon to differentiate player vs NPC dialogue\n- Change background color when `IsShowingPlayerResponse` is true\n- Add emotion icons next to option buttons (😠 🙂 🤔 etc.)\n\n**Suggested colors:**\n- NPC speaking: Dark gray/blue background\n- Player speaking: Slightly different shade or border color\n\n---\n\n## **Documentation References**\n\n### **UE 5.7 Specific Documentation:**\n\n1. **Data Tables and Structs:**\n   - [Data-Driven Gameplay Elements](https://dev.epicgames.com/documentation/en-us/unreal-engine/data-driven-gameplay-elements-in-unreal-engine?application_version=5.7)\n   - [Using Data Tables in UMG](https://dev.epicgames.com/documentation/en-us/unreal-engine/umg-ui-designer-quick-start-guide?application_version=5.7)\n\n2. **UMG Widget Communication:**\n   - [UMG UI Designer User Guide](https://dev.epicgames.com/documentation/en-us/unreal-engine/umg-ui-designer-user-guide?application_version=5.7)\n   - [Widget Interaction](https://dev.epicgames.com/documentation/en-us/unreal-engine/widget-interaction-component-in-unreal-engine?application_version=5.7)\n\n3. **Event Dispatchers (for passing data between widgets):**\n   - [Event Dispatchers](https://dev.epicgames.com/documentation/en-us/unreal-engine/event-dispatchers-in-unreal-engine?application_version=5.7)\n\n4. **Blueprint Communication:**\n   - [Blueprint Communication](https://dev.epicgames.com/documentation/en-us/unreal-engine/blueprint-communication-in-unreal-engine?application_version=5.7)\n\n5. **Delay and Timeline Nodes:**\n   - [Flow Control](https://dev.epicgames.com/documentation/en-us/unreal-engine/flow-control-in-unreal-engine?application_version=5.7)\n\n### **Dialogue System Design Patterns:**\n\nWhile not Unreal-specific, these patterns informed this solution:\n- **Choice-Based Dialogue Trees** - Standard pattern where player intent precedes exact dialogue\n- **Emotion/Tone Selection** - Common in RPGs (Mass Effect, Dragon Age, Fallout 4)\n\n---\n\n## **Summary of Changes:**\n\n| Asset | Changes Required |\n|-------|-----------------|\n| **Data Table Struct** | Add `OptionEmotion` and `PlayerDialogue` fields |\n| **DT_Dialogue** | Populate new fields for all rows |\n| **WB_Options** | Display `OptionEmotion`, store and pass `PlayerDialogue` |\n| **WB_Dialogue** | Add `ShowPlayerResponse` event, `PlayerCharacterName` variable |\n| **BP_NPC1** | Update `OptionSelected` to show player response before NPC response |\n\n---\n\nIf you enable \"Edit Existing Blueprints\" in settings, I can make these changes directly for you. Otherwise, follow the steps above to implement this emotion-based dialogue choice system manually.","state":"done"}],"role":"assistant","metadata":{"createdAt":"1769169335703"}}],"timestamp":"2026-02-26T10:09:38.531Z","messageCount":6}